AGI - The Italian Republic is "inserted today in the broadest community of the European Union > which we have decided to give life to the other free peoples of the continent and of which we will, within a few days, consecrate, with the election of the European Parliament, the sovereignty" > . The words are of the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella>, and are contained in a message sent to the prefects so that they interpret them in the initiatives promoted locally on the occasion of the celebration of the Day of the Republic. The message was released yesterday by Quirinale.<br> It is 9.43 a day later, when Senator Claudio Borghi, >candid to the Europeans in the Centro constituency, immediately after Roberto Vannacci and Susanna Ceccardi, protests on social media and directly attacks the head of the state. "It is June 2, is the Feast of the Italian Republic. Today the sovereignty of our nation is consecrated. If the president really thinks that the sovereignty is of the European Union instead of Italy, for consistency should resign - he asks -, because his function would no longer make sense>".<br> Several times during the day, then Borghi returns to intervene in order to defend the statement made, defining it "perfectly legitimate, almost granted". "If anyone wants to change Article 1 of the Constitution and write that sovereignty belongs to the EU rather than to the people has only to deposit a Constitutional bill. Then we'll see who votes," he adds. " Apparently the fans of 'More Europe' claimed to celebrate with Mattarella the 'consecration of the sovereignty of the European Union' >without anyone saying anything. I am sorry for them but we are here in full legitimacy to ask voters sent for 'More Italy and less Europe'. On TV, to those who ask for Borghi's tweet, Matteo Salvini says at first not to have read it >. But, after listening to the content, it does not distance itself, approving its concepts, while correcting and clarifying that the League "does not demand the resignation of anyone".&nbsp; "Borghi is our great senator. Simply today is June 2 and therefore national sovereignty comes before any other membership - says the head of Via Bellerio -. Then the Italians will choose the Europe they want, but with respect for all, starting from the Quirinale, today is the feast of the Italians". "I think that the head of the state has been misrepresented by some newspaper > - azzarda - because on the day of the feast of the Republic, on the day when the Constitution reminds us that sovereignty belongs to the people, talk of European sovereignty ..."<br> Frasi, those of the legists, which are not welcomed by the ally of Forza Italia Antonio Tajani.&nbsp;"We are Italian and European identity. This is our civilization. Every anti-European choice is deleterious for Italy," notes the blue vice premier, in a tweet posted in the evening. "Mattarella is good at highlighting our European perspective. I express my solidarity with him for the attacks he received."
"This festival is also important because we are in an electoral campaign for the European elections," Giorgia Meloni had predicted, in a reasoning made in the morning, speaking in the margin of the parade at the Imperial Forums. "And at the bottom of this festival also reminds us of the first idea of Europe, which was an idea of Europe that imagined that its strength, the strength of its union, was also the strength and specificity of the national states - he added the premier -. Perhaps we should return to that embryo of European idea and European dream." &nbsp;<br> In the hive of the centre, in addition to Tajani, Maurizio Lupi also intervenes directly to condemn the position of Borghi. "The attack on the President of the Republic is unacceptable and unqualified - says the President of Us moderate -. The League apologizes for these unbearable and unreasonable words to Sergio Mattarella guarantor of the National Unity and elected, I remember, even with the League vote”.&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Coral is the indignation of opposition to the words of Borghi>.&nbsp; The Pd, with the group leader Francesco Boccia, speaks of statements that show the "invasive force of the sovereign forces". Then the secretary dem Elly Schlein directly intervenes. President M5s Giuseppe Conte also stands. "It is very serious the attack >arrived by an exponent of the League, a political force that is part of the government, to President Mattarella on the day of the feast of the Republic," he says. "We ask that the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, take the distance," he adds. "It's an unworthy polemic, requesting President Mattarella's resignation is something unexplainable, so serious and so dismissed."
<div </div
<br The leader of Italy lives Matteo Renzi, > from his voice, is said "today more than ever I am proud to have indicated Sergio Mattarella as candidate for the Colle in 2015" e&nbsp; "to have blocked the design of Salvini al Papeete in 2019".
<div </div
&nbsp;
While Carlo Calenda of Action resorts to sarcastic attack >: "I realize that per&nbsp; Salvini is too complicated. The thing that Salvini should do is try at least to keep a decent and educated behavior because when we do not know what to say is best to silence".&nbsp;"The intolerance of a certain area (not small) of the right towards President Mattarella is the consequence of two aspects of their (in)political culture: the crude inspiration of sovereignism and the rejection of a figure of guarantee above the parties. The League and those who do not condemn it to the right are a danger to democracy," he complains, finally, Luana&nbsp;Zanella, group leader of Green Alliance and left to the House.
