"I'm reading things, I'm struggling to understand what language Giorgia Meloni is talking about, what movie she's seeing. See another country. The other day she attacked me after saying that the left erases identity, I replied that she does not realize that in a year and a half that governs is erasing people's freedom." The secretary replied to the words of Giorgia Meloni who resumed the statements of Nicolas Schmit according to which the conservatives would be a non-democratic force. "Because if you have a hunger wage - he added -, while she blocks the minimum wage, and you can't pay rent while she erases 330 million fund rent, if you can't cure yourself because they cut public health you don't have full freedom in this country. So we continue to nail this government on a gigantic social and wage issue that Meloni continues to try to evade with weapons of mass distraction and that the PD is not willing to accept."
&nbsp;
On the Milan stage, Schlein reiterated many of his positions in foreign policy. From the Middle East, "we immediately call for a ceasefire to stop the massacre in Gaza," to Europe and its commitments for peace, "we continue to believe in the solution of the two peoples and two states and we want a Europe that makes every diplomatic effort for this.&nbsp; Europe is born as a peace project and must remain a Europe of peace. Never war economy." And again:&nbsp; "In this continent nationalism has always produced one thing, war, and continues to produce it today so we will always be against every nationalism".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Schlein also admitted: "We were wrong as a centre-left not to reform citizenship when we had numbers to do it."&nbsp; Then she came back on the issues on which she focused much of the electoral campaign, such as the theme of health:&nbsp;"When we say more public health>, we are talking about more services, more perspectives of independent life for people with disabilities because trouble if we still hear from the right words of exclusion, discrimination or segregation of people with disabilities who have full right to inclusion in school and work." &nbsp;&nbsp;
According to the leader of the PD, moreover, "it is necessary to regulate short rentals to put stakes that avoid speculation. Otherwise in university cities prices pop up. A year and a half of nothing by the Meloni government" on home policies and "two weeks after the vote arrive with a building contract. The right to live is also fundamental for those who have to study."
&nbsp;
Then another fool to the premier about feminism and commitment to women: "We can't do anything about a female premier who doesn't care about other women. The only thing Giorgia Meloni did is to get anti-abortist doctors into the consultors." &nbsp;
