AGI - "In 1946 the choice of the Italian people for the Republic > wrote a decisive page of democracy > and laid the foundations for a renewed social pact, which would have found articulate in the Constitutional Charter". The President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella>, writes this in a message sent to the Prefects of Italy so that they interpret it in the initiatives promoted locally on the occasion of the celebration of the Day of the Republic.
&nbsp;
<h2>Mattarella: "Central-territory synergies weld the unit</h2>
"When a fruitful synergies between the local institutions and favored paths of connection between the center and the territories are woven, when - as happened in recent months - together emergencies are faced, when local authorities are supported in overcoming moments of administrative and financial crisis, the unity of the democratic building is strengthened, enhancing the principle of autonomy in the horizon of solidarity," the President of the Republic wrote.
&nbsp;
<h2> European: Mattarella, with the consecrated vote the sovereignty of the EU
The Italian republic is "inserted today in the wider community of the European Union which we have decided to give life to the other free peoples of the continent and of which we will consecrate, in a few days, with the election of the European Parliament, the sovereignty", Mattarella emphasized in the message sent to the Prefects of Italy.
&nbsp;
<h2> The facade of the building Chigi illuminated with the Tricolore</h2>
On the occasion of the 78th anniversary of the proclamation of the Republic, the main facade of Palazzo Chigi will be illuminated with the Italian tricolor, from 00:01 to dawn and from dusk at 23:59 on Sunday 2 June. Also, on Sunday's day, in Piazza Colonna will be the performance of the bands of the Armed Forces and Police Forces, from 14:30 and until 18:30.&nbsp;
